[2]
Date: Thu, 16 Feb 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Haaretz daily, 14 Feb 2005 [edited]
<http://www.haaretz.com/hasen/spages/682846.html>

The Veterinary Department of the Ministry of Agriculture on Tuesday
[14 Feb 2006] ordered the Diamond Pet Food company to remove its
entire range of products from the shelves.
The call came after test results confirmed that their dog food was
hazardous to the animals' health.
Agriculture ministry officials decided to withdraw their seal of
approval from the products and issue a warning to the general public.
They added that the ban applied to all the of the U.S.-based
company's products.
[Byline: Amiram Cohen]
